      "parameters": {
        "color": 4,
        "width": 704,
        "height": 2028,
        "content": "# üìò n8n Workflow: WhatsApp Bulk Message Broadcast via Google Sheets\n\n## üìå Overview\n\nThis **n8n automation workflow** enables you to send **bulk WhatsApp messages** directly from a **Google Sheet** using the **WhatsApp Business Cloud API**. It ensures efficient delivery and status tracking of each message, making it ideal for marketing, updates, or client communication.\n\n---\n\n## üîç Key Features\n\n- üì• Fetches live rows from a connected Google Sheet  \n- üì§ Sends personalized WhatsApp messages to each number  \n- üìù Updates the message delivery status back to the sheet  \n- üïí Supports batching and delays to comply with rate limits\n\n---\n\n## üß∞ Requirements\n\nBefore setting up the workflow, ensure you have:\n\n- ‚úÖ Access to the **WhatsApp Business Cloud API** (via Meta Developer account)  \n- ‚úÖ Google Sheets integration configured in n8n  \n- ‚úÖ A properly formatted Google Sheet (see below)  \n\nüìÑ [Sample Google Sheet Template](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1nI-AwIR3Y1FYzV0lwjr9iK6Ia4WuD5eRtgJH819rIIc/edit?usp=sharing)\n\n---\n\n## üìÑ Google Sheet Structure\n\n| WhatsApp No  | Message                     | Status  |\n|--------------|-----------------------------|---------|\n| +8801XXXXXXX | Hello, this is a test msg.  | (empty) |\n\n> ‚ÑπÔ∏è Keep the `Status` column blank for rows that need to be processed.\n\n---\n\n## ‚öôÔ∏è Workflow Configuration Steps\n\n### 1. üîó Connect to Google Sheets\n\n- Add the **Google Sheets** node  \n- Authenticate with your Google account  \n- Select the appropriate spreadsheet and worksheet  \n- Apply a filter: `Status is empty`\n\n### 2. üîÅ Loop Through Data in Batches\n\n- Use **SplitInBatches** or a **Code** node to process a defined number of rows (e.g., 5 per batch)  \n- Include a **Wait** node to delay (e.g., 0.1‚Äì0.5 seconds) between each request to avoid hitting rate limits\n\n### 3. üõ† Configure WhatsApp Business API\n\n- Add an **HTTP Request** node  \n- Authenticate using your Meta (Facebook) developer credentials  \n- Use a pre-approved **message template ID**  \n- Map Google Sheet columns to dynamic variables in the message payload\n\n### 4. üìã Update Message Status\n\n- After successfully sending each message, use the **Google Sheets Update** node  \n- Update the `Status` column to `Sent` or `Failed` based on the API response\n\n---\n\n## üéØ WhatsApp Template Requirements\n\nMake sure your template:\n\n- ‚úÖ Is approved by Meta  \n- ‚úÖ Uses variables (e.g., `{{1}}`, `{{2}}`) for dynamic values  \n- ‚úÖ Matches the message content format being sent\n\n---\n\n"
      },
